body:
@kallewoof I agree with the points mentioned and the rate limiting. The PR, in its current form gives a somewhat better error message in case the Faucet Transaction fails. 

However, I think it might be even better if we could update the faucet to return a Code **'429 Too many requests'** error when accessing the faucet more than once with the script, as suggested by @0xB10C [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/22565#discussion_r679049280) so that we can provide a more cleaner message to use the browser for multiple pay-outs. 

Let me know your views on it :)
